# AxOntology Project Rules

## Testing & Examples Requirements

### On Every Feature or Refactor
When adding a new feature or refactoring existing code:

1. **Update Integration Tests**
   - Add or update tests in `src/test/integration.test.ts`
   - Ensure new functionality is covered by test cases
   - Update existing tests if behavior changes
   - Run `npm test` to verify all tests pass

2. **Update Examples**
   - Add relevant examples in `examples/` directory
   - Update `examples/README.md` if adding new example categories
   - If the feature involves GraphQL, add query examples in `examples/queries/`
   - If the feature involves MCP, update `examples/mcp_examples.md`
   - Ensure examples demonstrate the real-world usage of the feature

3. **Update Documentation**
   - Update the main `README.md` if the feature affects the public API or usage
   - Update relevant design docs in `design_docs/` if architectural changes are made
   - Update `design_docs/DSL.md` if DSL syntax or semantics change
   - Update the PRD (`design_docs/Product Requirements Document (PRD).md`) if requirements change

## Documentation Standards

- Keep documentation synchronized with code changes
- Include code examples in documentation when explaining features
- Document breaking changes prominently
- Update API documentation for any interface changes

## Code Quality

- Follow existing patterns in the codebase
- Keep the adapter pattern consistent (`src/adapters/`)
- Maintain separation between core logic (`src/core/`) and GraphQL layer (`src/graphql/`)
- Ensure MCP server implementations follow the established patterns (`src/mcp/`)

## Testing Standards

- All new features must have integration tests
- Tests should be comprehensive and cover edge cases
- Use the test helpers in `src/test/testHelpers.ts` for consistency
- Ensure tests are maintainable and well-documented

## Before Completing Any Task

Always verify:
- [ ] Tests added/updated and passing
- [ ] Examples added/updated
- [ ] Documentation updated
- [ ] Code follows project patterns
